 <H1>Enforcing (Conflict) Serializability</H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Two-phase Locking (2PL) Protocol:
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Each Xact must obtain a S (shared) lock on object before reading, and an X (exclusive) lock on object before writing.
<LI>Once an Xact releases any lock, it cannot obtain new locks.
<LI> If an Xact holds an X lock on an object, no other Xact can get a lock (S or X) on that object.
</UL></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>2PL allows only conflict-serializable schedules.
</H2></P>

<P></UL><UL></P>

<P><LI><H2>Potential problem of deadlocks: we could have a cycle of Xacts, T1, T2, ... , Tn, with each Ti waiting for its predecessor to release some lock that it needs.
</H2></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI>Dealt with by killing one of them and releasing its locks.</UL></UL></P>

